SIMPLE: insurmountable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Insurmountable
<hw>In`sur*mount"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>surmountable</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>insurmountable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Incapable of being passed over,
surmounted, or overcome; insuperable; <as>as, <ex>insurmountable</ex>
difficulty or obstacle</as>.</def> <rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hope thinks nothing difficult; despair tells us that difficulty is
<qex>insurmountable</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>I. Watts.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Insuperable; impassable; invincible.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Insurmountableness</ent>⟦br⟧
